summary: Coming Home Parings: Tom Holland x Reader Summary: Tom comes home after a hard day on set, the reader helps calm him down....
body:
Coming Home

Parings: Tom Holland x Reader

Summary: Tom comes home after a hard day on set, the reader helps calm him down.

Warnings: none

You were sitting on the couch, catching up on TV in your favorite hoodie which belonged to Tom. You checked the clock on your phone, noticing it was getting relatively later and Tom still hadn’t answered your last text.

You knew he was filming late tonight, but Tom always made sure he would reach out to it whenever he could to let you know how much longer he would be. It wasn’t like him to go this long with radio silence.

Bringing you knees up to your chest, you chew on the inside of your cheek as you flip through the channels, but nothing grabs your attention. You debate for a while on whether or not you should send another text, but you don’t want to be too overbearing.

Your thoughts came to stop when you heard a rattling at the door. A sigh of relief rolled through your body as you saw Tom open the door, placing his keys on the counter.

“Hey,” you called out to him, bringing your legs back on the floor as you tried to get a glimpse of the look on his face, “I tried calling you earlier but-“

Tom cut you off by picking you up in one swift motion, throwing you over his shoulder without a single word. He carried you into the bed room, closing the door behind the both of you.

“Tom?” You called out to him, hearing him huffing and puffing through his throat as he tossed you gently onto the bed. Something didn’t feel right, and you could tell right away.

“I’m so fucking exhausted, y/n,” Tom finally said in a raspy voice as he tossed his t shirt off and threw it on the floor before joining you on the bed. He grabbed you by the waist, pulling you close as he nuzzled his nose into the back of your neck, “Work kicked my ass today,” he groaned into her neck, sending a tickle up your spine.

You closed your eyes as your hands found his, lacing them together as you tried your best to calm him down. His breath heavy against your neck as you felt his heart beat pounding against your back.

“I’m glad you’re home,” you finally whispered. You reached over and pressed a gently kiss to his cheek, feeling his breath relax with a hitch as his eyes fluttered closed.

Tom nodded slowly, smiling against the top of your head. He hated feeling this stressed, but coming home to this always made him feel better right away.

“I love you, y/n,” he said as his eyes started feeling heavier, the stress finally pulling him into a sleep. He pulled you closer to him as you tossed a blanket over the two of you, “Thank you,” he said in a low voice.

“I love you too, Tom,” you whispered back, cuddling under the blanket beside him.
